# UI and Map Interaction Rules — Starfield Starmap Explorer

## Layout

- The app is full-viewport: map canvas fills the screen, with a floating controls bar and overlaid panels.
- The map controls (`#mapControls`) are a floating bar — position and z-index must not be changed without checking for overlap with other overlays.
- The info panel (`#infoPanel`) is a floating overlay — it appears on system click and is hidden by default.
- Do not add persistent left/right sidebars that reduce the map viewport unless explicitly asked.
- Any new panels or sidebars must be collapsible so the full map remains visible.

## Map Canvas

- The starmap container is a full-viewport `div` transformed via CSS `translate` and `scale`.
- Map points (`.mappoint`) are absolutely positioned children of the container.
- Pan is applied via `transform: translate(x, y) scale(s)` on the container — not by moving individual points.
- Zoom range: define `MIN_SCALE` and `MAX_SCALE` constants (suggested: 0.2–4.0). Enforce them in the zoom handler.
- Map points placed outside the container's native dimensions may not be reachable at high zoom — this is a known constraint, not a bug.

## Map Points

- Each `.mappoint` renders: a difficulty icon (`.pictofont`), the system name (`.namesecondary`), a note icon (`.note-icon`), and a scan icon (`.scan-icon`).
- Difficulty tier classes: `.point1` (green, level 1), `.point2` (blue, level 2), `.point3` (yellow, level 3), `.point4` (red/orange, level 4+).
- Note icon: grey (`#6b7280`) when no note; yellow (`#fcd34d`) when a note exists.
- Scan icon: grey when unscanned; cyan (`#00bcd4`) when scanned.
- Explored state: typically shown by a visual change on the system label or icon (opacity, colour, or a checkmark). Define a consistent explored visual if not already present.
- Map point text must not wrap — use `white-space: nowrap` to prevent layout breaks at lower zoom levels.

## Controls Bar

- Zoom in / zoom out buttons adjust scale by a fixed step.
- "Folder" button triggers `chooseSaveFolder()`.
- "Save" button triggers `saveToFolder()`.
- Save file selector (`#saveFileSelect`) opens a previously saved `.json` file.
- Refresh button (`#refreshSavesBtn`) refreshes the save file list from the chosen folder.
- File input (`#openSaveFileInput`) is a hidden fallback for direct `.json` file open.
- Do not remove or rename these controls without updating all dependent JS.

## Info Panel

- Opens on system click; shows system name, description, explored/scanned status.
- Content is replaced on each new system click — that is expected.
- Must include a close button or close on second click.
- Should not obscure more than ~25% of the map viewport on desktop.

## Note Modal

- A centred overlay modal (`#noteModalOverlay` / `.note-modal`).
- Always pre-populate `#noteContent` with the current system's note before showing.
- Save: update `systemStates[id].note`, call `saveSystemStates()`, update the note icon on the map point, close modal.
- Cancel: discard changes, close modal, no state mutation.
- Must close on Cancel click and after Save.

## Progress Counter

- Displayed in the info panel or as a persistent floating element.
- Shows: total systems, explored count, scanned count.
- Must update immediately on any state change — no page reload required.

## Reset

- "Reset Exploration" button clears all `explored`, `scanned`, and `note` values in `systemStates`.
- Must prompt for confirmation before executing (use `confirm()` or `showMessageBox()`).
- Must call `saveSystemStates()` after reset.
- Must update all map point visuals and counters immediately.

## Toast / Message Notifications

- Use `showMessageBox(title, message)` for error messages and important confirmations.
- For lightweight confirmations (e.g. "Note saved"), a brief on-screen toast is preferred over a modal. Implement as a timed `div` that fades out.
- Do not use `alert()` except for the reset confirmation dialog.

## Dark Space Aesthetic — Non-Negotiable

- Background: `#0d1117` (near-black space)
- Surfaces (panels, modals): `bg-gray-800` / `bg-gray-900` (Tailwind) or equivalent dark greys
- Text: light grey / white (`text-gray-100`, `text-gray-200`)
- Accents: blue (`#2196f3`, `#93c5fd`), cyan (`#00bcd4`), yellow (`#fcd34d`) for interactive states
- No light mode. No white backgrounds on map-facing components.

## Minimap (if added)

- Small canvas or scaled thumbnail in a corner, showing approximate positions of all systems.
- Optional feature — not currently present. If added, must not overlap controls or info panel.
- Clicking the minimap should pan the main view to that region.
